manufacturer of stereo equipment 
under the agreement nihon university and the japanese 
industrialist chiyoji misawa will pay the mit lab 10 million over 
five years misawa is a builder interested in computercontrolled 
houses 
founded in 1985 the mit lab has been a center for scientists 
seeking new applications for computers holography television and 
other media researches and graduate students often dressed in 
jeans and tshirts work in an environment where creativity and 
science are allowed to mix freely 
among the mit projects is technology to send movies over 
telephone lines so people could dial a number and have a film 
transmitted directly to their tv set 
