survey refused to participate said dr james o mason assistant 
secretary for health in the department of health and human 
services 
but mason said the surveys tracking of trends if not the 
precise numbers of users is accurate because the survey has been 
administered the same way all 10 times since 1971 he also said the 
findings are similar to those of other studies 
the survey interviewed 9259 people age 12 and older from march 
12 to june 20 interviews were conducted in person but respondents 
completed their own answer sheets to assure them that their 
responses would remain confidential and anonymous the report says 
some in the drug treatment community stressed that use of drugs 
in some areas continues unabated 
