relations was made soviet ambassador to the united states in april 
and a time of several foreign service changes 
he had served in the soviet embassy in washington for 13 years 
before returning to moscow in 1983 where he was a deputy foreign 
minister responsible for the united nations and north america he 
later rose to become one of three first deputy foreign ministers 
