equality between moslems and christians as envisaged by the peace 
plan 
christians have had a 6to5 edge in parliament since 
independence from france in 1943 
the present parliament was elected in 1972 for a fouryear term 
the civil war which broke out in 1975 has prevented elections and 
the house has repeatedly renewed its mandate 
