resorts were closed by the bitter cold and strong winds in gallup 
nm schools and the airport were closed 
many schools in washington state canceled classes for the rest 
of the week as wind damage and high electricity demand left tens of 
thousands of people in the dark 
puget power is fighting a losing battle said tim ortner a 
sheriffs deputy in whatcom county on the canadian border wind 
is just ripping up trees all over the county they cant keep up 
with it 
farmers dragged out their winter arsenal of frost and 
snowfighting equipment 
there is the potential for real doom and gloom said bob 
perkins of the riverside county farm bureau in california they 
are using orchard heaters helicopters wind machines and 
irrigation to prevent damage 
the storms beneficiaries were businesses that profit from snow 
such as ski resorts in colorado and the california mountains 
the colorado avalanche information center issued an avalanche 
warning for colorados entire mountain area as winds gusted to 90 
mph in the southern mountains 
high winds blew snow and downed trees in mammoth lakes calif 
with up to 18 inches of snow falling on the mammoth mountain ski 
area in the sierra less than a week ago the resort opened a soup 
kitchen for seasonal workers left jobless by lack of snow 
santa maria calif had about 20 minutes of snow showers the 
first on record in that valley near the santa barbara county coast 
in idaho 5 inches of snow fell in boise in a 12hour period 
ending early thursday and mountain home had 6 inches 
by contrast erie pa which is used to shoveling out from 
canadian storms that ride across lake erie faces the prospect of a 
rare green christmas after getting only 56 inches of snow this 
season 
forecasters said the western cold would linger during the 
weekend with frost reaching southern california beach communities 
such as la jolla and heavy snow falling in mountain areas of 
northern arizona 
four traffic deaths in northern california five in oregon and 
one in oklahoma were blamed on slippery roads in washington a 
falling tree killed a bainbridge island man in his backyard and a 
man apparently froze to death at a transient encampment underneath 
a highwy along seattles waterfront 
