<TEXT>
the last statue of josef stalin to stand 
in a european capital was pulled down in pouring rain at the stroke 
of midnight thursday symbolizing the demise of stalinism 
throughout europe 
a crane hoisted the bronze statue of the soviet dictator onto a 
truck covered by a green cloth and lying on its back the monument 
was driven off to an undisclosed final destination 
the statues exit coincided with nexjime hoxhas losing her last 
important political post an official announcement said the 
68yearold widow of enver hoxha communist albanias stalinist 
founder retired because due to her age from chairmanship of the 
communistled democratic front 
the two events seemed meant to convey that albanias communist 
party is serious about abandoning its 46year legacy of harsh 
authoritarian rule 
the few people who witnessed the statues fall were happy to see 
it go although restrained by long repression from openly 
expressing their joy 
