gave no information about its program or leaders 
the democrats want their own daily to be called democratic 
renewal 
that probably will not be enough to counter communist efforts to 
maintain power 
the communists are playing tough cracking down on riots in four 
cities last week with a huge show of army and police force and 
handing out sentences of up to 20 years to those arrested 
the communists also seem likely to revamp themselves along 
reformist lines to confront the challenge from the new opposition 
mrs hoxhas loss of her last political position indicates alia 
is moving strongly against oldtime conservatives 
the communists are to hold a key meeting next wednesday when 
they are likely to announce a government reshuffle promised when 
the students first pushed for reform 
the communist partys election program also will be published at 
that time and democratic party spokesman genc pollo says he 
expects it to move the ruling party toward a more democratic path 
