mikhail s gorbachev shocked by his foreign 
ministers resignation denied thursday his presidency was slipping 
toward dictatorship and condemned eduard shevardnadze for quitting 
in a time of crisis 
in an emotional speech to parliament shevardnadze accused 
hardliners of undermining economic and political reforms that he 
and gorbachev had worked on since 1985 putting the nation on the 
road to dictatorship the nearly 2000 legislators sat in stunned 
silence 
reformers have gone and hidden in the bushes he told the 
parliament his voice trembling dictatorship is coming 
in a speech later a somber gorbachev denied soviet democracy 
was threatened and accused shevardnadze of abandoning the nation in 
a time of ethnic conflict separatist movements in the 15 republics 
and food shortages 
gorbachev has sought authority to bypass parliament and use 
presidential decrees to deal with some of the nations crises many 
conservative soviet officials have urged gorbachev to take on even 
more sweeping powers 
the loss of shevardnadze one of the soviet unions two 
politicians with international stature was bound to hurt gorbachev 
as he faces domestic conflict and critical foreign policy issues 
