a train slammed into a packed tour bus 
stalled on a rail crossing in southern taiwan on thursday killing 
25 people and injuring 35 authorities said 
police lowered the death toll saying earlier official reports 
of 42 dead and 14 injured were erroneous they attributed the 
mistake to chaos at the crash site 
railway police in kaohsiung about 230 miles south of taipei 
