the train did not derail after the collision he said 
wang fengtang a passenger on the bus said she managed to jump 
out of the bus and escape the explosion 
police said an initial investigation showed the bus apparently 
had passed the railway crossing in suburban kaohsiung and turned 
into an alley but backed onto the tracks when the driver found the 
alley too narrow 
in the previous worst bus accident 41 people were killed when a 
bus plunged into a river bank in central taiwan in 1986 
