near the eve of terry andersons sixth silent 
christmas in captivity his lot and that of five other americans 
held hostage in lebanon is shrouded still with no message of 
holiday hope for freedom 
the latest word from the administration is as so often before 
that there is no new information on prospects for their release 
and that the government is doing everything it can to get them out 
that is a familiar message and a jarring one to the families of 
the lebanon hostages who have just seen hundreds of american 
