outlaw retailers of stealing sales and jobs from midweek business 
and from the lawabiding majority 
major told the house of commons tuesday that the two sides 
should reach an agreement that could be the basis for reform 
he described the 1950s shops act which bars english and welsh 
stores from opening on sundays as bizarre he noted that scottish 
shops are allowed to trade on sundays 
like storeowners in the recessiontainted united states many 
merchants also are slashing prices before the traditional january 
sales period because theyre finding it the only way they can 
generate business 
at the same time retailers have reported a pickup in sales in 
recent days and are hoping for a lastminute surge 
december retail sales are expected to fall from a year ago the 
first decline since britains 198081 recession said roy 
maconochie an analyst with the london investment firm james capel 
and co 
the combination of heavy markdowns and belowtarget sales 
coinciding with rising costs do not bode well for profits 
maconochie said 
he recently downgraded his profit forecasts for many of 
britains top retailing companies whose shares then took a 
battering on londons stock exchange 
the economic slowdown and high interest rates mean more britons 
