china rebuked hong kongs leading bank thursday 
for plans to reorganize under a british holding company which has 
been viewed as a sign of eroding confidence in the colony that 
reverts to chinese rule in 1997 
the hongkong and shanghai banking corp which in some ways acts 
like hong kongs central bank because it issues more than half the 
local currency announced the reorganization monday 
the change reflected similar moves taken by hundreds of other 
hong kong companies fearing what may happen to the capitalist 
enclave in the transition to chinese sovereignty 
but the banks move was considered particularly significant 
because it is one of hong kongs most influential businesses 
we believe that as an important financial and commercial 
institution the hongkong and shanghai banking corp should see to 
it that any new measure it takes will help promote rather than 
undermine the stability and prosperity of hong kong foreign 
ministry spokesman li zhaoxing said 
the chinese government has all along worked to maintain the 
stability and prosperity of hong kong for the benefit of hong kong 
residents and the benefit of both china and the united kingdom 
li said 
william purves chairman of the bank said the decision to 
reorganize reflected the banks global reach and did not signal 
abandonment of the territory where it has flourished for 125 years 
under an agreement with britain the chinese have promised to 
preserve hong kongs way of life for at least 50 years beyond 1997 
but faith in that pledge was shaken by the june 1989 military 
crackdown on the prodemocracy movement in china confidence also 
has eroded because of bickering between china and britain over the 
exact terms of the takeover agreement 
