<TEXT>
a judge refused thursday to delay a japanese 
companys 66 billion buyout of entertainment giant mca inc and 
an attorney for the arizona company seeking to block the merger 
said he would appeal 
govideo inc a scottsdalebased distributor of a patented 
dualdeck vcr filed an antitrust action dec 6 claiming the mca 
buyout by matsushita electric industrial co violates us laws 
designed to encourage competition 
judge robert broomfield of us district court in phoenix denied 
govideos motion for a temporary restraining order saying he was 
simply not persuaded that the proposed merger is 
anticompetitive 
broomfield also said govideo failed to prove its claim that it 
would suffer irreparable damage were the restraining order not 
issued 
joseph alioto govideos san francisco lawyer said an appeal 
would be filed friday in the 9th circuit court of appeals in san 
francisco he said the court would be asked to stall the merger 
pending a final ruling 
if we do not prevail there we will file an appeal with the 
us supreme court alioto said and if we do not succeed in 
staying the merger we will proceed with the case and seek 
divestiture we will ask a judge to unscramble the egg that is 
about to be scrambled 
arguments during thursdays hearing on the temporary restraining 
order centered on whether the merger would cause irreparable damage 
to govideo and whether the company had to prove that it would 
suffer immediate losses 
alioto said he had to show only that there is a threat of 
significant damage 
the antitrust law is designed to block noncompetitive mergers 
before the damage actually is done he said 
dan schulman another govideo attorney said the mca buyout 
would hurt govideo and other electronics manufacturers by 
lessening competition 
the market will be altered so that anyone who goes into that 
market will be at a disadvantage anyone in that market will be at 
a disadvantage he said it will be more difficult for govideo 
to compete it will be more difficult for govideo to produce 
hardware for that market 
