bank of boston corp thursday predicted a 
substantial loss for the fourth quarter but said its 10 
centpershare dividend will not be cut 
ira stepanian chairman and chief executive officer said the 
fourthquarter loss would be substantial but said results were 
expected to be better than the third quarter the nations 15th 
largest banking company reported a thirdquarter net loss of 255 
million 
the prolonged deterioration in the commercial real estate 
markets and the ongoing downturn in the regional economy continue 
to adversely affect our operating results said stepanian 
however we are unwavering in our commitment in this 
environment to deal aggressively with credit issues and to maintain 
what we believe to be strong loan loss reserves he said 
first boston paid a 31 cent dividend in the second quarter 
the dividend is payable jan 25 1991 to stockholders of record 
on dec 31 1990 
in another costcutting measure stepanian said pay raises would 
be deferred for more than 5000 bank employees 
by early 1991 bank officials want to layoff 1500 employees 8 
percent of the companys worldwide work force of 18500 
