<TEXT>
federal express corp on thursday reported 
a slight earnings increase in the second fiscal quarter as the 
company tried to cut expenses to offset higher fuel prices 
the air freight companys earnings totaled 3747 million or 71 
cents per share on revenues of 199 billion in the same period 
in 1989 the company reported earnings of 37 million or 70 cents 
per share on revenues of 172 billion 
the company paid 55 percent more per average gallon of fuel 
compared with last year and 62 percent more than the first fiscal 
quarter 
total fuel expenses increased 73 million from the same period a 
year ago and 77 million compared to this years first quarter 
strict adherence to costcutting programs provided a partial 
offset to significantly higher fuel prices continuing 
international losses a weak economy and slower volume growth 
said frederick smith chief executive 
federal expresss total volume for the second quarter was nearly 
83 million packages up from about 77 million a year ago average 
revenue per package was 1759 up from 1652 for the same period 
last year 
